<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUN 93 / International Company News: Groupe Salomon advances 43%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GROUPE Salomon, one of Europe's leading ski equipment companies, continued
its recovery last year with a 43 per cent increase in net profits to
FFr94.8m (Dollars 16.8m) in the year to March 31 from FFr66.3m in the
previous year, writes Alice Rawsthorn in Paris.
The group, which has been restructured in the two years since the arrival of
a new management team led by Mr Jean-Francois Gautier, said it expected
profits to stabilise this year but to return to growth in 1994-1995 due to
its product development plans.
Salomon fell into the red two years ago after a series of poor skiing
seasons in the Alps. It returned to profit in the 1991-1992 financial year
and made further progress last year.
Turnover rose by 6.5 per cent to FFr3.15bn in 1992-1993 from FFr2.96bn in
1991-1992 with operating profits increasing by 53.6 per cent to FFr312m from
FFr202m.
The group's pre-tax profits doubled to FFr177.28m from FFr86.36m over the
same period.
The board proposed raising the dividend by 75 per cent, by paying a dividend
of FFr14.00 and a tax credit of FFr7.00.
</TEXT>
