1855, will become chairman of the new company trading under the Brown Knight
&amp; Truscott name. The combined turnover of group will be Pounds 10m.
Brown Knight incurred a pre-tax loss of Pounds 914,000 on sales of Pounds
7.1m in the year to end-March 1992.
The acquisition, believed to be worth about Pounds 1.5m, will create a
company with an estimated 10 per cent share of its specialist market.
