<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUN 93 / Head of German stock exchange issues plea for a takeover
code
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WALLER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR ROLF BREUER, the director responsible for Deutsche Bank's securities
activities, yesterday called for a law to regulate takeovers and mergers in
Germany.
Mr Breuer, who is also chairman of the German stock exchange, said that it
was no excuse to say there were relatively few takeovers on the German
equity markets.
Although many senior bankers privately condemn the lack of rules governing
takeovers, the financial establishment has tended to keep quiet on the
issue, reflecting fears that codification of takeover rules would encourage
a practice which is considered anti-social in Germany.
Analysts have also suspected that large German financial institutions have
benefited from the absence of rules. They have taken advantage of the fact
that it is possible to acquire control of a company by buying a simple
majority of the shares, without obligation to extend the offer to all
shareholders.
The remarks by a member of the board of Germany's biggest bank, made in the
context of a speech about the future development of 'Finanzplatz
Deutschland' - Germany as a financial centre - reflect the German financial
establishment's concern to bring regulations for the securities industry up
to international standards.
The focus at present is on the passage of legislation designed to make
insider dealing a criminal offence, and to introduce a German equivalent of
the US Securities &amp; Exchange Commission (SEC).
The absence of such laws was seen as a failing, especially by foreign
investors in the German market. For that reason the proposed laws should be
adopted as soon as possible, Mr Breuer said.
The package of new laws will bring disclosure requirements into line with UK
and US practice. At present companies only have to disclose share stakes
when they reach between 20 and 25 per cent, in contrast to 3 per cent in the
UK. There are no current plans to introduce a takeover code.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>DEZ  Germany, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
