FT  22 JUN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Lords' Maastricht motion withdrawn
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE House of Lords will not have an opportunity to debate whether there
should be a referendum on the Maastricht treaty until after the bill has
completed its detailed committee stage discussion.
The amendment to the legislation, which was tabled earlier this month by a
cross-party group of peers, has been withdrawn because of difficulties about
its drafting.
The government is expected to announce today that there will be an extra two
days to debate the bill's committee stage, for which well over 400
amendments have been tabled.
