<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUN 93 / Engineering pay freezes for 1-in-5
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MORE THAN one in five engineering workers in South Yorkshire and the north
Midlands have accepted pay freezes in the past 12 months, the Sheffield
Association of the Engineering Employers' Federation said yesterday.
In the year ended May 31, about 22 per cent of the 350 companies in the
association negotiated pay freezes.
More than 40 per cent settled for pay rises of up to 2 per cent. Although a
quarter settled at between 3.1 per cent and 4 per cent, nearly all those
were concluded almost a year ago.
