FT  22 JUN 93 / World News in Brief: Warning in vain
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A pilot vessel tried for 45 minutes to warn the Panamanian ship Western
Winner that it was dangerously near BP's British Trent tanker, a Belgian
regional minister said. The two ships collided on June 3 and nine people
died on the tanker in the fire that followed.
