FT  21 JUN 93 / International Company News: Digital sells US leasing
business
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DIGITAL Equipment, the computer manufacturer, is to sell its US leasing
business to GE Capital, the fast-growing financial services arm of General
Electric, writes Martin Dickson.
The companies declined to disclose financial terms of the deal but GE will
take over servicing Digital's leasing customers and the unit's 40 employees.
GE Capital is one of the largest leasing organisations in the US.
