FT  21 JUN 93 / International Company News: Clarke Nickolls cuts losses
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Clarke Nickolls &amp; Coombs, the property investment and trading company, saw
its pre-tax losses fall from Pounds 727,000 to Pounds 47,000 in the 1992
year. The figures were helped by an exceptional credit of Pounds 79,000
against a charge of Pounds 948,000 for the fall in property values.
The accounts were produced on a going concern basis pending the resolution
of talks with Banque Indosuez over loans to an offshoot.
A tax credit left a net profit of Pounds 147,000 (Pounds 661,000 losses) but
there was a further provision of Pounds 642,000 (Pounds 6.83m) against
losses on withdrawal from property development.
Earnings per share were 0.71p (losses 3.2p).
