<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUN 93 / People: British Coal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Kevan Hunt, 55, director of employee relations at British Coal, is taking
over as chairman of British Coal Enterprise, the arm of the industry charged
with creating new employment opportunities in former mining areas.
Hunt, a member of the British Coal board, will replace John Northard, who is
retiring after 50 years in the coal industry.  Hunt was a founding director
of BCE in 1984 when it was launched to help staff cope with the shrinking
market for coal.  In the last nine years it claims to have created 80,000
jobs.  Another of its roles is to help former employees seek work outside
the industry.  Hunt said that BCE would be investing Pounds 50m in coalfield
areas in the coming year.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>British Coal Enterprise.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P7361 Employment Agencies.
</IN>
<XX>
